The paper deals with a robotics problem involving pick-and-place operations, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes an algorithmic pipeline for solving the problem, which involves optimization objectives and computational complexity, indicating a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem involves objects placed on a flat surface, which could involve computer vision techniques for object recognition and localization, making computer vision (cs.CV) a possible sub-category. The use of a robot to perform the pick-and-place operations suggests a control systems perspective, making systems and control (cs.SY) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a reduction-based approach to solving the problem, which could involve machine learning techniques for optimization, making machine learning (cs.LG) a possible sub-category as well.
